Version 1.20.0
--------------
    * Build with Go 1.25.2 (#324)

Version 1.19.0
--------------
    * Enable `go_library` to compile packages containing large numbers of files (#320)

Version 1.18.0
--------------
    * Migrate to `go_repo` and upgrade golang.org/x packages (#316)

Version 1.17.0
--------------
    * Build with Go 1.24.1

Version 1.16.0
--------------
    * Switch to using `go tool covdata` for test coverage reports

Version 1.15.2
--------------
    * Fully remove `get` subcommand (#309)

Version 1.15.1
--------------
    * Use more specific names for coverage variables to avoid clashes

Version 1.15.0
--------------
    * Add support for Go 1.23 coverage generation (#294)

Version 1.14.0
--------------
    * Remove support for Go <= 1.19 coverage generation (#291)

Version 1.13.0
--------------
    * Search for Go headers in toolchain provided by Go tool (#276)

Version 1.12.0
--------------
    * Add ability to set build labels with generate tool

Version 1.11.0
--------------
    * Support calling the `go tool cover` binary directly

Version 1.10.6
--------------
    * packageinfo files correctly account for stdlib vendoring

Version 1.10.5
--------------
    * upgrade x/mod to support new directives

Version 1.10.4
--------------
    * correctly pass the path flag to gensymabis

Version 1.10.3
--------------
    * Support assembly correctly for Go 1.22 (#227)
    * ldflags ordering is now correctly maintained (#231)

Version 1.10.2
-------------
    * Fix regression in 1.10.0 where module requirements passed in through `go_repo` were
      ignored.

Version 1.10.1
--------------
    * .a files in the directory of a Go package in a go_repo are now attached as dependencies

Version 1.10.0
-------------
    * Inspect both the host repo and the module's go.mod when resolving dependencies in the
      `generate` command.

Version 1.9.2
-------------
    * Generate correct paths for subdir imports within a module.

Version 1.9.1
-------------
    * Generate information allowing the package driver to work for go_repo within a test

Version 1.9.0
-------------
    * Generate correct subrepo info for package driver (#191)

Version 1.8.5
--------------
    * in go_repo, add c source to the generated cgo_library (#213)

Version 1.8.4
--------------
    * in go_repo's subrepo write build tags to the plz config

Version 1.8.3
--------------
    * only set cover false on go_library rules

Version 1.8.2
--------------
    * go_repo generated rules have coverage false

Version 1.8.1
-------------
    * Bug fixes in please_go generate

Version 1.8.0
-------------
    * Add --build_tag flag to `generate` subcommand to allow specifying a build tag to use when
      generating the BUILD files (#199)

Version 1.7.0
-------------
    * Allow selecting the pkg-config tool via PKG_CONFIG_TOOL env var

Version 1.6.2
--------------
    * Avoid adding go_binary targets to the install list for go_repo (#184)
    * Avoid adding host repo to labels if the label already has a subrepo for
      deps passed to `go_repo()` (#185)

Version 1.6.1
-------------
    * Handle cases where subrepo's using a `package_root` would cause duplicate package paths in the
      package info `.json` file (#177)

Version 1.6.0
-------------
    * Add `generate_module_version` command, which generates the file formerly
      generated by `go_mod_download`'s `#modinfo` target and optionally allows
      the given module path and version strings to be validated (#171)

Version 1.5.0
-------------
    * When generating the BUILD files for go_repo, discover targets providing imports in .importconfig files before
      resolving using the naming convention. This allows go_repo to depend on go_module.

Version 1.4.4
-------------
    * Don't set `_module` on go_binary commands in `go_repo`

Version 1.4.3
-------------
    * Don't try and pipe test output as it doesn't flush when the TestMain calls os.Exit

Version 1.4.2
-------------
    * Don't run the tests if the user has defined a TestMain in 1.20+

Version 1.4.1
-------------
    * Fix issue where we'd compile the parent directory if the package can't be found

Version 1.4.0
-------------
    * Add support for passing in a path to a modfile instead of using the modfile from the proxy

Version 1.3.3
-------------
    * please_go generate - skip over generating BUILD files for private directories
      i.e. directories that start with underscores

Version 1.3.2
-------------
    * Improve handling of the install arg on `generate` subcommand

Version 1.3.1
-------------
    * Stop parsing import comments

Version 1.3.0
-------------
    * Add install argument to the generate subcommand. This will be used by `go_get` to
      produce a filegroup that will be returned from the target to avoid having to
      specify each package individually with a subrepo build label.
    * Many fixes to the generate subcommand to better handle cases in the root of go modules

Version 1.2.0
-------------
    * Support for Go 1.20's coverage redesign

Version 1.1.2
-------------
    * Misc fixes for generating package info (#63)

Version 1.1.1
-------------
    * Fixes package generation for go_library actions with Go files in subdirectories

Version 1.1.0
-------------
    * Adds support to generate go rules for a given package (#49)

Version 1.0.0
-------------
    * Add subcommands to generate package info files used to supply
      an external go package driver (#48)

Version 0.1.4
-------------
    * Fix packages with assembly for Go 1.19 (#32)

Version 0.1.3
-------------
    * Handle embedding directories by name correctly (#28)

Version 0.1.2
-------------
    * Handle when test targets have no tests #20

Version 0.1.1
-------------
    *  Fix file names

Version 0.1.0
-------------
    *  Initial release
